### [Julia Lake](/company/team/#julia.lake) - Director, [Security Risk and Compliance](/handbook/engineering/security/#assure-the-customer---the-security-assurance-sub-department)
Joined GitLab April 2020 / Connect with Julia on [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/julia-lake-16843740/)

![Julia Lake](/images/blogimages/working-in-security/jlake_blog2.png){: .shadow.small.left.wrap-text}

**What do you do and who do you collaborate with in your role?**
I am responsible for the Security Assurance sub-department, which includes the security compliance, security operational risk and field security functions. Security Assurance is part of the [Security department](/handbook/engineering/security/#security-department), which is part of the broader [Engineering organization](/handbook/engineering/) at GitLab, and we work cross-functionally across the entire organization. We are extremely focused on information security and partner with system and process owners in order to ensure security controls and best practices are embedded throughout our environment. We also support our customers in their assessment of GitLab‚Äôs security practices and provide feedback from the field to drive internal security strategy.

**What are some projects you‚Äôre working on?**
As an organization, some recent projects we‚Äôve embarked on include: SOC 2 Type 2 and SOC 3 audit and report reviews, third party GRC application deployment, customer and sales enablement program development, and deployment of an operational risk management function.  Personally, I‚Äôve been focused on organizational strategy and roadmapping, policy definition and metric redesign.

**What‚Äôs something new and/or exciting that you‚Äôd like to learn about or be involved in?**
I‚Äôm always interested in learning more about the different functions of security. Lately I‚Äôve been particularly fascinated in learning more around Zero Trust architecture and best practices and am slowly making my way through [NIST 800-207](https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-207/final).

**If someone was interested in a role like yours, what‚Äôs the most helpful piece of advice you could offer?**
Go for it! Security is so incredibly dynamic and you can choose a career path that aligns with your specific interests. Security Assurance is especially interesting to me because we are truly leading the charge on helping organizations grow and mature their security posture, and we have the opportunity to partner with our wonderful customers along the way. My biggest piece of advice for Security Assurance professionals is to challenge yourself against complacency, be adaptive to change and think critically about how new requirements can be applied to meet intent without hindering the business. Also, good documentation is a shield.

